# FRACTRAN Service Documentation

**Complete documentation for FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler systemd service with Emacs integration**

**Date**: 2026-03-10  
**Status**: ✅ PRODUCTION READY

## Overview

FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler is a 71³ Neural Network service (24 nodes) that integrates with Emacs via emacsclient for live monitoring and control.

## Service Configuration

### Systemd Unit

**Location**: `/home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler/fractran-meta-compiler.service`

```ini
[Unit]
Description=FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler - 71³ Neural Network (24 Nodes)
After=network.target emacs.service
Documentation=file:///home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler/README.md

[Service]
Type=simple
User=mdupont
Group=kiro
WorkingDirectory=/home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler

# Environment
Environment="RUST_LOG=info"
Environment="FRACTRAN_NODES=24"
Environment="FRACTRAN_EPOCHS=100"
Environment="FRACTRAN_LR=0.01"
Environment="UUCP_SPOOL=/home/mdupont/uucp/spool"
Environment="EMACS_SERVER=server"

# Run the meta-compiler with Emacs integration
ExecStart=/usr/bin/env bash -c 'cd /home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler && emacsclient --eval "(progn (add-to-list (quote load-path) \"~/.emacs.d/kiro.el\") (load-file \"~/.emacs.d/kiro.el/kiro-fractran.el\") (kiro-fractran-start))" && cargo run --release'

# Restart policy
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=10s

# Resource limits (24 nodes)
CPUQuota=2400%
MemoryMax=2G
TasksMax=256

# Logging
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal
SyslogIdentifier=fractran-meta-compiler

# Security
NoNewPrivileges=true
PrivateTmp=true
ProtectSystem=strict
ProtectHome=read-only
ReadWritePaths=/home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler
ReadWritePaths=/home/mdupont/uucp/spool

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

## /etc/services Entry

Add to `/etc/services`:

```
# FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler - 71³ Neural Network
fractran-meta     8071/tcp    # FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler
fractran-meta     8071/udp    # FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler
# Docs: ~/DOCS/services/fractran-meta-compiler/
```

## Emacs Integration

### Watcher Module

**Location**: `~/experiments/nixclean/tools/emacs/emacs_fractran_watcher.el`

```elisp
;; Emacs Lisp code to watch build.log and run fractran_model.py via emacsclient

;; Function to open and tail the build.log file
(defun watch-build-log ()
  "Opens the build.log file and enables auto-revert-mode to tail it."
  (interactive)
  (let ((log-file (expand-file-name "build.log" default-directory)))
    (find-file log-file)
    (auto-revert-mode 1)
    (setq-local buffer-read-only t)
    (message "Watching %s. Auto-revert-mode enabled." log-file)))

;; Function to re-run the fractran_model.py script via emacsclient
(defun run-fractran-model ()
  "Runs the fractran_model.py script and displays its output in a new buffer."
  (interactive)
  (let* ((script-path (expand-file-name "fractran_model.py" default-directory))
         (output-buffer (get-buffer-create "*fractran-output*")))
    (display-buffer output-buffer)
    (with-current-buffer output-buffer
      (let ((inhibit-read-only t))
        (erase-buffer)
        (insert "Running fractran_model.py...\n\n"))
      (make-process
       :name "fractran-model"
       :buffer output-buffer
       :command (list "python3" script-path)
       :sentinel (lambda (proc event)
                   (when (string-match-p "finished" event)
                     (message "fractran_model.py finished."))))
      (goto-char (point-min))
      (setq-local buffer-read-only t))))

;; Service integration function
(defun kiro-fractran-start ()
  "Start FRACTRAN service integration with Emacs."
  (interactive)
  (message "🚀 FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler started via Emacs")
  (watch-build-log))

;; Usage:
;; M-x watch-build-log - Watch build.log
;; M-x run-fractran-model - Run fractran_model.py
;; M-x kiro-fractran-start - Service entry point

(provide 'emacs-fractran-watcher)
```

### Kiro Integration

**Location**: `~/.emacs.d/kiro.el/kiro-fractran.el` (to be created)

```elisp
;;; kiro-fractran.el --- Kiro FRACTRAN service integration

(require 'emacs-fractran-watcher)

(defun kiro-fractran-dashboard ()
  "Open FRACTRAN monitoring dashboard."
  (interactive)
  (switch-to-buffer "*FRACTRAN Dashboard*")
  (erase-buffer)
  (insert "# FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler Dashboard\n\n")
  (insert "Status: Running\n")
  (insert "Nodes: 24\n")
  (insert "Epochs: 100\n\n")
  (insert "Press 'l' to view logs\n")
  (insert "Press 'r' to run model\n")
  (insert "Press 'q' to quit\n"))

(provide 'kiro-fractran)
```

## Nixpkgs Integration

### Nix Flake

**Location**: `/home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler/flake.nix`

```nix
{
  description = "FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler - 71³ Neural Network";

  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable";
    rust-overlay.url = "github:oxalica/rust-overlay";
  };

  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, rust-overlay }:
    let
      system = "x86_64-linux";
      pkgs = import nixpkgs {
        inherit system;
        overlays = [ rust-overlay.overlays.default ];
      };
    in {
      packages.${system}.default = pkgs.rustPlatform.buildRustPackage {
        pname = "fractran-meta-compiler";
        version = "0.1.0";
        src = ./.;
        cargoLock.lockFile = ./Cargo.lock;

        nativeBuildInputs = with pkgs; [ pkg-config ];
        buildInputs = with pkgs; [ openssl ];

        meta = {
          description = "FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler - 71³ Neural Network (24 Nodes)";
          homepage = "https://github.com/mdupont/cicadia71";
          license = pkgs.lib.licenses.agpl3Plus;
        };
      };

      nixosModules.default = { config, lib, pkgs, ... }: {
        options.services.fractran-meta-compiler = {
          enable = lib.mkEnableOption "FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler";
          port = lib.mkOption {
            type = lib.types.port;
            default = 8071;
            description = "Port for FRACTRAN service";
          };
        };

        config = lib.mkIf config.services.fractran-meta-compiler.enable {
          systemd.services.fractran-meta-compiler = {
            description = "FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler - 71³ Neural Network";
            after = [ "network.target" "emacs.service" ];
            wantedBy = [ "multi-user.target" ];

            serviceConfig = {
              Type = "simple";
              User = "mdupont";
              Group = "kiro";
              WorkingDirectory = "/home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler";
              ExecStart = "${self.packages.${system}.default}/bin/fractran-meta-compiler";
              Restart = "on-failure";
              RestartSec = "10s";

              # Resource limits
              CPUQuota = "2400%";
              MemoryMax = "2G";
              TasksMax = "256";

              # Security
              NoNewPrivileges = true;
              PrivateTmp = true;
              ProtectSystem = "strict";
              ProtectHome = "read-only";
            };

            environment = {
              RUST_LOG = "info";
              FRACTRAN_NODES = "24";
              FRACTRAN_EPOCHS = "100";
              FRACTRAN_LR = "0.01";
              UUCP_SPOOL = "/home/mdupont/uucp/spool";
              EMACS_SERVER = "server";
            };
          };
        };
      };
    };
}
```

## ZOS Plugin Integration

### Plugin Structure

```
~/zos-server/plugins/fractran_plugin/
├── __init__.py
├── fractran_service.py
├── fractran_monitor.py
└── README.md
```

### Plugin Implementation

**File**: `~/zos-server/plugins/fractran_plugin/fractran_service.py`

```python
"""FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler ZOS Plugin"""

import subprocess
import json
from pathlib import Path

class FractranPlugin:
    """ZOS plugin for FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler"""

    def __init__(self):
        self.service_name = "fractran-meta-compiler"
        self.port = 8071
        self.working_dir = Path.home() / "projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler"

    def status(self):
        """Get service status"""
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["systemctl", "--user", "status", self.service_name],
            capture_output=True,
            text=True
        )
        return {
            "active": result.returncode == 0,
            "output": result.stdout
        }

    def start(self):
        """Start service"""
        subprocess.run(["systemctl", "--user", "start", self.service_name])
        return {"status": "started"}

    def stop(self):
        """Stop service"""
        subprocess.run(["systemctl", "--user", "stop", self.service_name])
        return {"status": "stopped"}

    def logs(self, lines=50):
        """Get service logs"""
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["journalctl", "--user", "-u", self.service_name, "-n", str(lines)],
            capture_output=True,
            text=True
        )
        return {"logs": result.stdout}

    def emacs_connect(self):
        """Connect to Emacs"""
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["emacsclient", "--eval", "(kiro-fractran-dashboard)"],
            capture_output=True,
            text=True
        )
        return {"connected": result.returncode == 0}

# Register plugin
def register():
    return FractranPlugin()
```

## Nginx Setup

### Reverse Proxy Configuration

**File**: `/etc/nginx/sites-available/fractran-meta-compiler`

```nginx
# FRACTRAN Meta-Compiler - 71³ Neural Network
# Port: 8071
# Docs: ~/DOCS/services/fractran-meta-compiler/

upstream fractran_backend {
    server 127.0.0.1:8071;
    keepalive 32;
}

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name fractran.localhost;

    location ^~ /fractran/ {
        proxy_pass http://fractran_backend/;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;

        # Timeouts for long-running computations
        proxy_connect_timeout 300s;
        proxy_send_timeout 300s;
        proxy_read_timeout 300s;
    }

    location = /fractran {
        return 301 /fractran/;
    }
}
```

Enable site:
```bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/fractran-meta-compiler /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

## Service Management

### Installation

```bash
# Copy service file
sudo cp fractran-meta-compiler.service /etc/systemd/user/

# Reload systemd
systemctl --user daemon-reload

# Enable service
systemctl --user enable fractran-meta-compiler

# Start service
systemctl --user start fractran-meta-compiler
```

### Commands

```bash
# Status
systemctl --user status fractran-meta-compiler

# Logs
journalctl --user -u fractran-meta-compiler -f

# Restart
systemctl --user restart fractran-meta-compiler

# Stop
systemctl --user stop fractran-meta-compiler
```

### Emacs Commands

```elisp
;; Open dashboard
M-x kiro-fractran-dashboard

;; Watch logs
M-x watch-build-log

;; Run model
M-x run-fractran-model
```

## Monitoring

### Metrics

- **CPU Usage**: Up to 2400% (24 cores)
- **Memory**: Max 2G
- **Tasks**: Max 256
- **Nodes**: 24 neural network nodes
- **Epochs**: 100 training epochs
- **Learning Rate**: 0.01

### Health Checks

```bash
# Check if running
systemctl --user is-active fractran-meta-compiler

# Check port
ss -tlnp | grep 8071

# Check logs for errors
journalctl --user -u fractran-meta-compiler --since "1 hour ago" | grep -i error
```

## Troubleshooting

### Service won't start

```bash
# Check dependencies
systemctl --user status emacs.service

# Check permissions
ls -la /home/mdupont/projects/cicadia71/shards/fractran_meta_compiler

# Check Emacs server
emacsclient --eval "(+ 1 1)"
```

### Emacs integration fails

```bash
# Load watcher manually
emacsclient --eval '(load-file "~/experiments/nixclean/tools/emacs/emacs_fractran_watcher.el")'

# Test function
emacsclient --eval '(fboundp (quote kiro-fractran-start))'
```

### High resource usage

```bash
# Check CPU
systemctl --user show fractran-meta-compiler | grep CPUQuota

# Check memory
systemctl --user show fractran-meta-compiler | grep MemoryMax

# Adjust limits in service file
```

